                <h1>Anubis: The Guardian of the Afterlife</h1>
                <p>Anubis, the ancient Egyptian god of the afterlife, is often depicted as a jackal or a figure with a jackal's head. He played a vital role in embalming and guiding souls through the Underworld. Revered for his protective qualities, Anubis oversees mummification rituals and ensures the weighing of the heart ceremony for a peaceful afterlife.</p>
